        <num>CC 1329</num>
        <heading>1329.  Parties plaintiff and defendant</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1329.  Parties plaintiff and defendant.
The suit for partition ought to be instituted by the heir who wishes the division; the coheirs or their representatives must be cited, in order that the partition may be ordered, and the form thereof determined, if there should be any dispute in this respect.</p>
        </content>
